<p align="center"><font face="Courier New">What

started out as a Direct3D learning experience evolved into a simple

space shooter inspired by the classic 1980 arcade game called Rip-Off.</font></p>

<p align="center"><font face="Courier New">Your

goal is to protect the 10 fuel pods from the pirate ships. You are

given unlimited lives to accomplish your mission but once all 10 pods

are gone the game is over. To help you accomplish your goal you are

given 3 weapons:</font></p>

<p align="center"><font face="Courier New">The

<b><i>Laser Cannon</i></b> which is a rapid

fire pulse laser (your primary weapon)</font></p>

<p align="center"><font face="Courier New">The

<b><i>Nuke</i></b> which destroys all pirate

ships within a certain radius</font></p>

<p align="center"><font face="Courier New">And

finally <i><b>Heat Seeking Missiles</b></i>

with unlimited range</font></p>

